  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Lebanon Crisis 2020 - MS Response and Recovery</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Objective: To support 975 individuals/195 HH to fulfil their basic needs, improve their living conditions, and increase overall wellbeing and dignity of life following the Beirut Blast. 
Outcomes: 1) Increased food security during a two-month period, 2) Improved health, hygiene and living conditions during a two-month period</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">One-off conditional cash assistance for  975 individuals (approximately 195 blast-affected and vulnerable households) in Bourj Hammoud, in the form of vouchers worth 60 USD/person (50 USD food and 10 USD for hygiene and sanitation materials). Maximum level of support is 300 USD/household.</narrative>
  </description>
